author: @kirillfedtsov
text: I came here because I needed to filter and order some csv files on backend and then send filtered\ordered csv files back. First I figured csv module is probably what I need but it's actually useless for ordering and filtering. Then I though I will just export everything into postgres, filter it there and then export it back into csv. And strangely enough the best way to export csv into postgres using python was suggested to be with pandas! And then I though: 'wait, why do I even need sql if I can manage my data in a dataframe and export  it back into csv'. So here I am! Excited to learn!  Alex, thanks for the video!
